conditional statements:
-->to make the set of instructions(block of code)(conditional block)execute only when the given condition is true 
-->used to decide whether the code has to be executed or skip based on the given condition
-->line-line(sequence)
Block of code:
-->it will execute only when that specific condition is true
Condition: An expression that will evaluates an result(true/false)
ex:console.log(5>6)
Methods:
if 
if-else
else if
switch

ternary operators
if: Only one possible condition 
-->if the condition is true it will execute other wise it will skip
syntax:
if(condition){
--block of code
}
